###Block: Hydra Abilities
# Ability Name	Unique Key				Category of Ability		Type								Define				Description																												Choose												Modify VAR						Source Page		Aspects							Description of the Benefits																																																																																																													Temporary effect description
Fast Healing	KEY:Fast Healing ~ Hydra	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.ModifyHP	DEFINE:FastHealingRate|0	DESC:A hydra's fast healing ability is equal to its current number of heads (minimum fast healing 5). This fast healing applies only to damage inflicted on the hydra's body.																					SOURCEPAGE:p.178	ASPECT:Ability Benefit|%1|FastHealingRate		BENEFIT:A hydra's fast healing ability is equal to its current number of heads (minimum fast healing 5). This fast healing applies only to damage inflicted on the hydra's body. A hydra regains hit points at %1 per round. Fast healing does not restore hit points lost from starvation, thirst, or suffocation, nor does it allow a creature to regrow lost body parts. Unless otherwise stated, it does not allow lost body parts to be reattached. Fast healing continues to function (even at negative hit points) until a creature dies, at which point the effects of fast healing end immediately.|FastHealingRate
Hydra Traits						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary								DESC:A hydra can be killed by severing all of its heads or slaying its body.																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.178	ASPECT:Ability Benefit|(%1 heads)|HydraHeads	BENEFIT:A hydra can be killed by severing all of its heads or slaying its body. Any attack that is not an attempt to sever a head affects the body, including area attacks or attacks that cause piercing or bludgeoning damage. To sever a head, an opponent must make a sunder attempt with a slashing weapon targeting a head. A head is considered a separate weapon with hardness 0 and hit points equal to the hydra's HD. To sever a head, an opponent must inflict enough damage to reduce the head's hit points to 0 or less. Severing a head deals damage to the hydra's body equal to the hydra's current HD. A hydra can't attack with a severed head, but takes no other penalties.
Regenerate Head	KEY:Regenerate Head ~ Hydra	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary								DESC:When a hydra's head is destroyed, two heads regrow in 1d4 rounds.																		CHOOSE:NUMBER|MIN=-5|MAX=5|TITLE=Add or subtract a number of hydra heads	BONUS:VAR|HydraHeads|%CHOICE|PREAPPLY:PC	SOURCEPAGE:p.178									BENEFIT:When a hydra's head is destroyed, two heads regrow in 1d4 rounds. A hydra cannot have more than twice its original number of heads at any one time. To prevent new heads from growing, at least 5 points of acid or fire damage must be dealt to the stump (a touch attack to hit) before they appear. Acid or fire damage from area attacks can affect stumps and the body simultaneously. A Multiple angry snake-like heads rise from the sleek, serpentine body of this terrifying monster. hydra doesn't die from losing its heads until all are cut off and the stumps seared by acid or fire.																TEMPDESC:Use this temporary bonus to add heads (and bite attacks) to the Hydra reflecting newly grown heads.

###Block: Intellect Devourer Abilities
# Ability Name				Unique Key						Category of Ability		Type								Description																										Source Page		Description of the Benefits
Detect Magic				KEY:Detect Magic ~ Intellect Devourer	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.SpellLike.Sense			DESC:The Intellect Devourer can Detect Magic as a constant ability.																SOURCEPAGE:p.180
Body Thief					KEY:Body Thief ~ Intellect Devourer		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural			DESC:An intellect devourer can reduce its size, crawl into the mouth of a helpless or dead creature, and burrow into the victim's skull to devour its brain.	SOURCEPAGE:p.180	BENEFIT:As a full-round action that provokes an attack of opportunity, an intellect devourer can reduce its size, crawl into the mouth of a helpless or dead creature, and burrow into the victim's skull to devour its brain. This is a coup de grace attempt that inflicts 8d4+3d6+8 points of damage. If the victim is slain (or already dead), the intellect devourer usurps control of the body and may use it as its own, as if it controlled the target via a dominate monster spell. The intellect devourer has full access to all of the host's defensive and offensive abilities save for spellcasting and spell-like abilities (although the intellect devourer can still use its own spell-like abilities). A host body may not have been dead for longer than 1 day for this ability to function, and even successfully inhabited bodies decay to uselessness in 7 days (unless this time is extended via gentle repose). As long as the intellect devourer occupies the body, it knows (and can speak) the languages known by the victim and basic information about the victim's identity and personality, yet has none of the victim's specific memories or knowledge. Damage done to a host body does not harm the intellect devourer, and if the host body is slain, the intellect devourer emerges and is dazed for 1 round. Raise dead cannot restore a victim of body theft, but resurrection or more powerful magic can.
Vulnerable to Protection from Evil	KEY:Intellect Devourer Vulnerablities	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.Weakness	DESC:An intellect devourer is treated as a summoned creature for the purpose of determining how it is affected by a protection from evil spell.				SOURCEPAGE:p.180

